		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi, there!
<br />
<br />Supposing I'm going to put some roms on cartridges:
<br />
<br />The TV system at my country is PAL-M (different from japanese PAL). So I'm supposing native consoles follows this system.
<br />
<br />So, what are the problems I can have in putting NTSC roms to play on PAL-M consoles? We had national versions of the original NES, and carts are plain compatible, but I dunno. And the national consoles plays whatever you put in them (China, Japan, USA carts...)
<br />
<br />Thanks in advance.

		

